WEBVTT

00:04.338 --> 00:05.439
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:05.506 --> 00:07.007
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

00:07.075 --> 00:09.877
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:09.943 --> 00:11.312
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:11.379 --> 00:12.480
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

00:12.546 --> 00:15.516
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:15.583 --> 00:17.418
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:17.485 --> 00:18.686
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

00:18.752 --> 00:21.755
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:21.822 --> 00:23.357
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:23.424 --> 00:24.825
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

00:24.892 --> 00:28.096
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:29.830 --> 00:31.165
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

00:31.232 --> 00:34.034
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

00:35.469 --> 00:39.907
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

00:39.973 --> 00:41.142
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:41.209 --> 00:42.543
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

00:42.610 --> 00:45.546
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:45.613 --> 00:46.947
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:47.014 --> 00:48.149
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

00:48.216 --> 00:51.285
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:51.352 --> 00:52.986
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

00:53.053 --> 00:54.188
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

00:54.255 --> 00:56.657
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

00:56.724 --> 01:00.594
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:00.661 --> 01:03.564
* WHAT'S NEW,
SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:27.488 --> 01:28.656
HUH?

01:33.661 --> 01:35.596
WHO--WHO'S THERE?

01:35.663 --> 01:38.699
YOU KNOW ME WELL ENOUGH,
AKIRA ONODERA.

01:38.766 --> 01:42.636
THE NEW WHARF YOU WANT
TO BUILD FOR YOUR FACTORY

01:42.703 --> 01:46.039
IS A THREAT TO OUR
SIMPLE WAY OF LIFE.

01:46.106 --> 01:51.279
THINGS IN THIS VILLAGE
HAVE NOT CHANGED FOR
HUNDREDS OF YEARS.

01:51.345 --> 01:54.348
YOU CANNOT HOLD BACK
PROGRESS, ANCIENT ONE.

01:54.415 --> 01:56.250
SINCE ANCIENT TIMES,

01:56.317 --> 02:00.721
THIS VILLAGE HAS HAD
ITS OWN FORM OF PROTECTION.

02:02.523 --> 02:04.525
THAT'S NOTHING
BUT AN OLD LEGEND.

02:04.592 --> 02:08.296
WE SHALL SEE WHAT
IS LEGEND AND WHAT IS REAL

02:08.362 --> 02:13.267
WHEN YOUR ACCURSED FACTORY
LIES IN RUBBLE AROUND YOU,

02:13.334 --> 02:16.837
CRUSHED BY THE FEET
OF A GIANT MONSTER!

02:16.904 --> 02:20.140
HA HA HA HA!

02:28.449 --> 02:29.950
Professor: HERE TO UNVEIL
HER INVENTION,

02:30.017 --> 02:33.787
THIS YEAR'S UNANIMOUS
AGE-APPROPRIATE
SCIENCE SUPERSTAR,

02:33.854 --> 02:37.625
MY VERY OWN PRIZE PUPIL,
VELMA DINKLEY.

02:42.996 --> 02:45.098
NO WAY. NOT AGAIN.

02:45.165 --> 02:46.500
THAT'S NOT FAIR.

02:46.567 --> 02:49.337
BETTER LUCK
NEXT TIME, ELLIOT.

02:49.403 --> 02:50.838
THANK YOU,
PROFESSOR POMFRIT.

02:50.904 --> 02:54.475
IT'S A THRILL TO FINALLY
UNVEIL DOGBOT,

02:54.542 --> 02:59.347
THE WORLD'S FIRST
FULLY FUNCTIONAL
ROBOTIC CANINE.

02:59.413 --> 03:02.316
A DOG? YOU'VE GOT
TO BE KIDDING ME.

03:02.383 --> 03:05.085
I HATE DOGS. I'M ALLERGIC.

03:05.152 --> 03:07.154
BUT, LIKE,
WE ALREADY HAVE A DOG.

03:07.221 --> 03:08.222
REAH.

03:08.289 --> 03:09.490
UNLIKE SOME DOGS,

03:09.557 --> 03:11.559
DOGBOT IS INCAPABLE OF FEAR,

03:11.625 --> 03:14.962
AND NOT ONLY DOES DOGBOT
NOT REQUIRE FOOD OR SLEEP...

03:19.233 --> 03:20.401
HE CAN PROVIDE IT.

03:20.468 --> 03:22.169
MAYBE THAT TIN-PLATED TERRIER

03:22.236 --> 03:23.937
ISN'T ALL BAD AFTER ALL,
HUH, SCOOB?

03:24.004 --> 03:25.339
HMPH!

03:25.406 --> 03:26.807
Professor Pomfrit: AND AS
THE GRAND PRIZE WINNER,

03:26.874 --> 03:29.710
WE'RE TAKING YOU
AND 4 OF YOUR CLOSEST FRIENDS

03:29.777 --> 03:33.046
TO PRESENT DOGBOT
TO THE FAMOUS ROBOTICS EXPERT,

03:33.113 --> 03:36.617
DR. AKIRA ONODERA
IN TOKYO, JAPAN.

03:36.684 --> 03:37.651
OHH...

03:40.621 --> 03:42.323
Professor Pomfrit:
THERE'S MOUNT FUJI,

03:42.390 --> 03:43.824
AND THE OSAKUSA TEMPLE

03:43.891 --> 03:47.428
AND THE OLD
TAKAMOTO MOVIE STUDIO.

03:47.995 --> 03:49.897
[YAWNS]

03:49.963 --> 03:54.902
PROFESSOR, YOU KNOW JAPAN
LIKE I KNOW THE LAYOUT
OF MY REFRIGERATOR.

03:54.968 --> 03:56.337
I SHOULD, SHAGGY.

03:56.404 --> 03:59.139
DR. ONODERA AND I
STUDIED TOGETHER YEARS AGO

03:59.206 --> 04:01.041
AT THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO.

04:01.108 --> 04:02.910
SHAGGY? SHAGGY?

04:02.976 --> 04:04.177
JET LAG.

04:04.244 --> 04:06.780
I'M AFRAID SHAGGY
DOESN'T TRAVEL TOO WELL.

04:06.847 --> 04:08.582
[SNORES]

04:08.649 --> 04:10.984
VELMA, YOU ARE INDEED
A ROLE MODEL

04:11.051 --> 04:13.487
FOR THE NEXT GENERATION
OF AUTOMATION ENGINEERS.

04:13.554 --> 04:15.022
THANK YOU, DR. ONODERA,

04:15.088 --> 04:20.027
BUT DOGBOT IS NOTHING
COMPARED TO YOUR
ROBOTIC MARVELS.

04:20.093 --> 04:24.097
Ancient One:
DISHONOR OUR VILLAGE
BY BUILDING THAT WHARF,

04:24.164 --> 04:30.404
AND THESE METAL
MONSTROSITIES WILL LIE
CRUSHED UNDER YOUR FEET.

04:30.471 --> 04:33.707
YOU CHOSE TO IGNORE
MY WARNING, ONODERA.

04:33.774 --> 04:37.144
NOW, SUFFER
THE ANCIENT CURSE!

04:37.210 --> 04:40.448
I SEE NO GIANT MONSTERS,
ANCIENT ONE.

04:40.514 --> 04:45.653
TRUE, FOR IT IS YOU
YOURSELF WHO WILL
BECOME THE MONSTER.

04:45.719 --> 04:49.189
EACH NIGHT,
WHEN YOU FALL ASLEEP,

04:49.256 --> 04:52.893
YOU WILL TRANSFORM
INTO A GIANT CREATURE

04:52.960 --> 04:58.766
AND DESTROY YOUR OWN
HATEFUL CREATIONS!

04:59.867 --> 05:03.937
DOGBOT, EXTRA LARGE
TERIYAKI PIZZA, NOW!

05:08.342 --> 05:10.444
WHAT WAS ALL
THAT ABOUT, AKIRA?

05:10.511 --> 05:12.513
JUST SOME OLD MYSTIC
FROM THE VILLAGE

05:12.580 --> 05:14.848
TRYING TO SCARE ME
WITH A PHONY CURSE.

05:14.915 --> 05:17.117
HE THINKS
I'M DISHONORING HIS TOWN

05:17.184 --> 05:18.318
BY BUILDING A WHARF.

05:18.386 --> 05:19.687
WELL, THANKS TO VELMA,

05:19.753 --> 05:22.322
THE ONLY THING
HE CURSED WAS THAT PIZZA.

05:24.758 --> 05:25.959
MMM.

05:27.728 --> 05:28.462
[GULPS]

05:28.529 --> 05:30.898
SHAGGY ATE THE CURSED PIZZA!

05:30.964 --> 05:32.366
CURSED?!
[GULPS]

05:32.433 --> 05:34.034
DON'T WORRY,
SHAGGY-SAN.

05:34.101 --> 05:36.136
HE IS ONLY
A CRAZY OLD MAN.

05:36.203 --> 05:38.972
THE PROBABILITY
OF YOUR TURNING
INTO A MONSTER

05:39.039 --> 05:41.375
WHILE YOU SLEEP
IS SLIM.

05:43.844 --> 05:46.614
Akira: YOU ARE
ALL MOST WELCOME
AT MY GUEST HOUSE.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.916
I HOPE YOU WILL
SLEEP WELL.

05:52.052 --> 05:53.320
HUH?

05:53.387 --> 05:55.288
THIS?

05:55.355 --> 05:57.991
THIS IS ONE SERIOUS CHAIN,
SCOOBY-DOO.

05:58.058 --> 05:59.560
I'M STAYING RIGHT HERE,

05:59.627 --> 06:01.128
EVEN IF I DO
CHANGE INTO A MONSTER,

06:01.194 --> 06:02.162
WHICH I WON'T

06:02.229 --> 06:04.264
'CAUSE I'M NOT
FALLING ASLEEP.

06:04.331 --> 06:06.066
[YAWNS]

06:06.133 --> 06:08.736
I DON'T CARE
HOW JET LAGGED...

06:08.802 --> 06:10.771
[SNORES]

06:12.039 --> 06:13.040
RAGGY?

06:14.274 --> 06:16.143
OHH...

06:16.209 --> 06:17.678
NIGHT, NIGHT.

06:27.721 --> 06:30.458
[ROARING]
ZOINKS!

06:30.524 --> 06:32.893
AAH!
AAH!
AAH!

06:37.498 --> 06:40.468
[ROARING]
ZOINKS!

06:49.843 --> 06:52.746
ZOINKS!

06:53.681 --> 06:55.449
[SCOOBY AND SHAGGY SNORE]

06:55.516 --> 06:57.951
Velma: GOOD MORNING,
SLEEPY HEADS.

06:58.018 --> 07:00.387
YOU WERE SO TIRED
FROM JET LAG
LAST NIGHT,

07:00.454 --> 07:01.722
WE HAD DOGBOT
RUSTLE YOU UP

07:01.789 --> 07:03.223
SOME BREAKFAST
IN BED.

07:03.290 --> 07:04.992
REAH!

07:05.058 --> 07:06.627
[YAWNS]

07:06.694 --> 07:09.196
THANKS, BUT I'M REALLY
NOT THAT HUNGRY.

07:09.262 --> 07:10.731
HUH?
HUH?
HUH?

07:10.798 --> 07:12.700
LIKE, DID I
JUST SAY THAT?

07:12.766 --> 07:14.134
LET US HOPE,
SHAGGY-SAN,

07:14.201 --> 07:17.237
THAT YOUR HUNGER
WAS NOT SATISFIED
LAST NIGHT...

07:17.304 --> 07:19.507
BY DEVOURING
THE VILLAGE.

07:19.573 --> 07:21.509
THE VILLAGE?
VILLAGE?
THE VILLAGE?

07:21.575 --> 07:23.711
MY HUMBLE APOLOGIES
FOR THE INTRUSION.

07:23.777 --> 07:27.147
I AM LIEUTENANT
KEIKO TANAKA
OF THE TOKYO POLICE.

07:27.214 --> 07:29.550
A 30-FOOT MONSTER
ATTACKED BOTH
THE VILLAGE

07:29.617 --> 07:31.619
AND THE FACTORY
LAST NIGHT.

07:34.021 --> 07:34.922
LIEUTENANT TANAKA,

07:34.988 --> 07:37.357
YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY THINK
IT WAS SHAGGY.

07:37.424 --> 07:38.892
IT DEFIES ALL LOGIC.

07:38.959 --> 07:41.495
YEAH, LIKE, I WAS HERE
IN BED ALL NIGHT,

07:41.562 --> 07:44.331
AND I CHAINED MYSELF UP
FOR GOOD MEASURE.

07:44.397 --> 07:46.800
[ALL GASP]

07:46.867 --> 07:49.469
LOOKS LIKE THIS CHAIN
HAS BEEN BITTEN THROUGH

07:49.537 --> 07:51.471
BY RAZOR SHARP TEETH.

07:51.539 --> 07:54.608
ZOINKS!
I AM A MONSTER!

07:59.813 --> 08:03.817
GANG, I THINK WE'VE GOT
ANOTHER MYSTERY
ON OUR HANDS.

08:03.884 --> 08:07.621
WELL, AT LEAST SHAGGY'S
MONSTROUS APPETITE
HAS RETURNED.

08:07.688 --> 08:09.256
SHAGGY'S NO MONSTER.

08:09.322 --> 08:13.093
THERE'S GOT TO BE A LOGICAL
EXPLANATION FOR ALL OF THIS.

08:13.160 --> 08:16.229
WHAT'S THE LOGICAL
EXPLANATION FOR THAT?

08:18.131 --> 08:19.132
Shaggy: ZOINKS!

08:20.868 --> 08:23.904
HA! THAT IS THE SOUND
OF THE MONSTER.

08:23.971 --> 08:26.373
THE ANCIENT ONE
PUT HIS CURSE ON YOU!

08:26.439 --> 08:28.842
YOU DESTROYED
OUR VILLAGE!

08:28.909 --> 08:29.977
UH-OH.

08:33.513 --> 08:34.682
SHAGGY-SAN,

08:34.748 --> 08:37.384
A TOURIST JUST TURNED IN
AN AMATEUR VIDEO

08:37.450 --> 08:39.620
OF THE MONSTER
AND...WELL...

08:39.687 --> 08:40.954
IN LIGHT OF NEW EVIDENCE,

08:41.021 --> 08:44.057
I'M AFRAID I MUST
TAKE YOU INTO CUSTODY.

08:44.124 --> 08:45.626
UH-OH.

08:51.064 --> 08:53.801
COME ON, EVERYBODY.
HOLD TIGHT.

08:55.202 --> 08:58.572
Velma: JINKIES!

08:58.639 --> 09:00.908
LIKE, THANKS AGAIN,
DOGBOT.

09:00.974 --> 09:03.777
YOU ARE ONE HANDY
HEAVY METAL POOCH!

09:03.844 --> 09:07.347
WOW! THIS IS WHAT I CALL
RAPID TRANSIT.

09:07.414 --> 09:09.516
THIS IS THE BULLET
TRAIN, FREDDY,

09:09.583 --> 09:10.918
AND JUDGING
FROM MY HAIR,

09:10.984 --> 09:13.887
I'D SAY WE'RE GOING
210 MILES AN HOUR!

09:13.954 --> 09:16.790
WE'VE GOT TO FIND A WAY
INSIDE!

09:22.596 --> 09:24.164
SO, LIKE,
JUST TO REVIEW,

09:24.231 --> 09:26.266
I'M TURNING INTO
A MONSTER EVERY NIGHT,

09:26.333 --> 09:28.936
AND WE'RE, LIKE,
ON THE RUN FROM
THE AUTHORITIES.

09:29.002 --> 09:30.137
THAT'S BAD.

09:30.203 --> 09:33.406
BUT WE DID MANAGE TO FIND
THE DINING CAR.

09:33.473 --> 09:34.742
THAT'S GOOD!

09:34.808 --> 09:36.076
WE'LL KEEP YOU
OUT OF SIGHT

09:36.143 --> 09:37.244
UNTIL WE GET TO THE
BOTTOM OF THIS MYSTERY.

09:37.310 --> 09:38.946
DON'T LOOK NOW,

09:39.012 --> 09:41.514
BUT WE'RE GONNA NEED
SOMEONE TO KEEP US
OUT OF SIGHT.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.784
Velma: IT'S
LIEUTENANT TANAKA!

09:49.422 --> 09:51.191
GOTCHA!

09:51.258 --> 09:53.093
WHO-OA-OA!

09:56.664 --> 09:58.165
WHOA!
WHOA!
WHOA!

10:04.304 --> 10:05.673
NICE GOING, DOGBOT.

10:05.739 --> 10:07.507
YOU REALLY ARE
MAN'S BEST FRIEND.

10:07.574 --> 10:09.109
AND GIRL'S, TOO.

10:09.176 --> 10:10.510
[JEALOUS GROWL]

10:10.577 --> 10:13.246
WELL, THAT DETECTIVE LADY
IS LIKE MAN'S WORST FRIEND.

10:13.313 --> 10:15.716
SHE'S NOT GONNA GIVE UP
UNTIL SHE NABS US.

10:15.783 --> 10:16.950
DON'T WORRY, SHAGGY.

10:17.017 --> 10:18.652
NOW THAT WE'RE IN
DOWNTOWN TOKYO

10:18.719 --> 10:20.153
SURROUNDED BY MILLIONS
OF PEOPLE,

10:20.220 --> 10:22.222
WE'LL JUST MELD
INTO THE SCENERY.

10:22.289 --> 10:23.724
4 AMERICAN
TOURISTS,

10:23.791 --> 10:25.726
A GREAT DANE,
AND A ROBOT--

10:25.793 --> 10:28.461
SURE, FRED,
WE'LL BLEND
RIGHT IN.

10:28.528 --> 10:31.832
Shaggy: YEAH, WE STAND OUT
LIKE A SORE SUSHI ROLL.

10:31.899 --> 10:33.533
LIKE, COULD THINGS
GET ANY WORSE?

10:33.600 --> 10:35.669
YOU SHOULD NEVER
ASK THAT, SHAGGY.

10:35.736 --> 10:37.470
THINGS CAN ALWAYS
GET WORSE.

10:37.537 --> 10:39.773
HELLO,
VELMA DINKLEY.

10:39.840 --> 10:42.309
ELLIOT?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN JAPAN?

10:42.375 --> 10:45.212
I MADE MY FOLKS
TAKE ME HERE AS
A CONSOLATION PRIZE

10:45.278 --> 10:48.716
FOR HAVING MY AWARD
STOLEN FROM ME BY YOU!

10:48.782 --> 10:50.583
VELMA'S NO THIEF,
ELLIOT.

10:50.650 --> 10:52.485
MAYBE, MAYBE NOT.

10:52.552 --> 10:54.688
BUT HE'S DEFINITELY
A MONSTER.

10:54.755 --> 10:57.324
HEY, POLICE,
OVER HERE!

10:57.390 --> 10:58.258
[WHISTLES]

10:58.325 --> 11:00.227
WE'RE TOO EASY TO SPOT.

11:00.293 --> 11:01.494
NOT FOR LONG.

11:01.561 --> 11:03.731
QUICK,
INTO THAT ALLEY!

11:03.797 --> 11:05.232
[WHISTLES BLOW]

11:11.872 --> 11:15.008
ARE YOU BLIND?
THAT'S THEM
RIGHT THERE.

11:15.075 --> 11:17.644
THERE THEY ARE.
GET THEM!

11:17.711 --> 11:20.313
SO, YOU THOUGHT
YOU COULD ESCAPE ME?

11:20.380 --> 11:21.849
WHAT DO YOU SAY NOW?

11:21.915 --> 11:24.718
LIKE, SAYONARA!

11:24.785 --> 11:27.721
[POP SONG
IN JAPANESE PLAYING]

12:18.705 --> 12:20.607
THAT TANAKA
DOESN'T GIVE UP.

12:20.673 --> 12:21.909
WE'VE GOT TO GET
OFF THE STREET

12:21.975 --> 12:23.777
BEFORE SHE
FINDS US AGAIN.

12:23.844 --> 12:26.413
HEY, LIKE, CHECK OUT
THAT CRAZY HOTEL.

12:26.479 --> 12:28.916
LET'S CHECK INTO
THAT CRAZY HOTEL.

12:28.982 --> 12:30.951
WE NEED
A PLACE TO CRASH.

12:32.585 --> 12:34.054
OKAY, WE'RE ALL SIGNED IN.

12:34.121 --> 12:36.957
MR. SMITH, MS. VON SMITH,
MS. SMYTHE,

12:37.024 --> 12:38.892
AND ME,
MR. SHECKELMAN.

12:38.959 --> 12:40.427
UH, LIKE,
NO OFFENSE, FRED,

12:40.493 --> 12:44.064
BUT I THINK
I'D BETTER
SLEEP IN THERE.

12:44.131 --> 12:47.267
YOU KNOW HOW RESTLESS
I GET IN MY SLEEP.

12:47.334 --> 12:50.938
UH, YOU WANT TO SLEEP
IN THE HOTEL VAULT,
MR. SHECKELMAN?

12:51.004 --> 12:52.873
THAT IS HIGHLY
UNORTHODOX.

12:52.940 --> 12:55.042
I'M SHECKELMAN,
HE'S SMITH.

12:55.108 --> 12:57.644
THAT WOULDN'T BE
TOO MUCH TROUBLE,
WOULD IT?

12:57.710 --> 13:00.013
MY FRIEND JUST WANTS
TO FEEL SAFE.

13:07.154 --> 13:09.089
WHEW!

13:09.156 --> 13:12.559
IF THESE ROOMS
WERE ANY SMALLER
THEY'D BE DRAWERS.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.294
IT'S A TOKYO
TUBE HOTEL, FREDDY,

13:14.361 --> 13:16.463
WHERE THE ECONOMICAL
MEETS THE CRAMPED.

13:16.529 --> 13:20.067
SORRY, SCOOBY,
IT'S TOO CROWDED IN HERE
FOR THE BOTH OF US.

13:20.133 --> 13:22.669
YOU CAN STAND GUARD
OUT THERE.

13:22.735 --> 13:24.504
[WHIMPERING]

13:24.571 --> 13:25.572
DON'T WORRY, SCOOB.

13:25.638 --> 13:26.840
WHAT COULD
POSSIBLY HAPPEN

13:26.907 --> 13:29.209
IN A SAFE, MODERN CITY
LIKE TOKYO?

13:29.276 --> 13:30.810
[CRASH]

13:32.312 --> 13:34.114
JINKIES! LOOK!

13:37.951 --> 13:39.752
[LOUD FOOTSTEPS]

13:39.819 --> 13:40.921
JEEPERS!

13:40.988 --> 13:41.955
UH, GUYS?

13:42.022 --> 13:43.556
DON'T LOOK NOW,

13:43.623 --> 13:47.127
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
SHAGGY REALLY IS
THE MONSTER!

13:47.194 --> 13:48.228
NO!

13:54.767 --> 13:57.104
WOW!
THAT WAS TOO CLOSE.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.972
QUICK, HE'S MAKING
A RUN FOR IT.

13:59.039 --> 14:00.440
WE'VE GOTTA
FOLLOW HIM.

14:03.710 --> 14:06.880
SHAGGY SURE WALKS
A LOT FASTER
WITH 20-FOOT LEGS.

14:06.947 --> 14:08.581
BUT HOPEFULLY NOT
FOR MUCH LONGER.

14:08.648 --> 14:09.749
THE SUN'S COMING UP.

14:09.816 --> 14:12.185
HE SHOULD RESUME
HIS HUMAN FORM.

14:15.322 --> 14:17.524
[SNORING]

14:20.928 --> 14:22.930
JUST 5 MORE MINUTES.

14:22.996 --> 14:24.864
Velma:
SHAGGY, WAKE UP.

14:24.932 --> 14:26.633
BREAKFAST!

14:28.568 --> 14:32.305
HA HA HA! SO I GUESS
YOU WERE KIDDING
ABOUT BREAKFAST, HUH?

14:32.372 --> 14:34.307
HEY, I'M SURPRISED
YOU'RE STILL HUNGRY.

14:34.374 --> 14:37.410
WE WATCHED YOU DEVOUR
HALF OF TOKYO LAST NIGHT.

14:37.477 --> 14:39.913
HERE, SHAGGY.
GOOD THING I TOOK
THE LIBERTY

14:39.980 --> 14:42.215
OF PACKING
EMERGENCY OUTFITS.

14:43.650 --> 14:44.717
I GUESS THIS IS IT--

14:44.784 --> 14:46.219
TIME TO TURN ME IN.

14:46.286 --> 14:48.221
OH, NO.
NOT A CHANCE.
NO.

14:49.957 --> 14:52.192
LIKE, FACE IT.
WE'RE FAR FROM HOME,

14:52.259 --> 14:54.061
I'M TURNING INTO
A MONSTER EVERY NIGHT,

14:54.127 --> 14:56.263
AND WE DON'T HAVE
A FRIEND TO TURN TO.

14:56.329 --> 14:57.430
THAT'S NOT
QUITE TRUE.

14:57.497 --> 15:00.233
THERE IS ONE PERSON
WHO CAN HELP US.

15:02.102 --> 15:03.903
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

15:03.971 --> 15:06.673
HMM? VELMA,
THANK GOODNESS.

15:06.739 --> 15:07.874
YES, OF COURSE
I'LL HELP,

15:07.941 --> 15:09.276
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO BE
VERY CAREFUL.

15:09.342 --> 15:11.011
I'LL MEET YOU
THIS AFTERNOON.

15:11.078 --> 15:13.380
KAMINARI GATE
AT OSAKUSA TEMPLE.

15:13.446 --> 15:15.848
IT'S SECLUDED
AND EASY TO FIND.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.617
LIEUTENANT TANAKA
WILL NEVER THINK

15:17.684 --> 15:19.119
OF LOOKING FOR YOU
THERE.

15:25.825 --> 15:27.194
Fred: I GOT TO HAND IT
TO YOU, DAPH,

15:27.260 --> 15:29.529
ONLY YOU COULD CREATE
THESE GREAT DISGUISES

15:29.596 --> 15:32.099
WITH JUST A STAPLER
AND BLACK MASCARA.

15:32.165 --> 15:33.666
AH, THERE IT IS!

15:33.733 --> 15:35.302
OSAKUSA TEMPLE.

15:39.672 --> 15:40.807
HMMPH!

15:40.873 --> 15:42.809
HEY, THERE'S
PROFESSOR POMFRIT.

15:42.875 --> 15:44.011
LET'S GO MAKE CONTACT.

15:44.077 --> 15:47.447
BUT GANG,
PLAY IT REAL COOL.

15:47.514 --> 15:50.383
EXCUSE ME...
PROFESSOR POMFRIT?

15:50.450 --> 15:51.851
YES?
IT'S US!

15:51.918 --> 15:54.454
FRED, DAPHNE, VELMA,
SHAGGY, AND SCOOBY.

15:54.521 --> 15:55.688
WE'RE IN DISGUISE.

15:55.755 --> 15:57.857
Tanaka: YOU CALL
THAT A DISGUISE?

15:57.924 --> 16:00.927
ALL I HAD WAS MASCARA
AND A STAPLER.

16:00.994 --> 16:02.762
IT'S A TRAP!
GET OUT OF HERE, KIDS!

16:02.829 --> 16:05.665
DOGBOT,
SUPER JUMBO POPCORN, STAT!

16:07.567 --> 16:08.735
TAKE COVER!

16:12.939 --> 16:14.041
THIS IS POPCORN!

16:14.107 --> 16:16.209
AFTER THEM!
HURRY!

16:19.779 --> 16:21.314
RUH-OH!

16:23.416 --> 16:25.152
DOGBOT, CAN YOU
TURN INTO SOMETHING

16:25.218 --> 16:26.619
THAT'LL GET US
OUT OF HERE?

16:32.459 --> 16:33.460
YIKES!

16:35.395 --> 16:36.496
UGH.

16:36.563 --> 16:40.067
LIKE, SO SLEEPY.

16:40.133 --> 16:41.768
MUSTN'T SLEEP.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.203
TURN INTO MONSTER.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.872
[SNORING]

16:45.938 --> 16:47.107
HUH?

16:47.174 --> 16:50.310
HEY, CHECK OUT
THIS TINY LITTLE CAR.

16:51.244 --> 16:53.213
ZOINKS! OH, NO!

16:53.280 --> 16:55.748
LIKE, I'M A BIG
GIANT MONSTER!

16:55.815 --> 16:57.717
[WHIMPERS]
I'M ALL ALONE!

16:57.784 --> 16:59.519
I'M ALL ALONE!

17:02.189 --> 17:04.557
WHAT A BUMMER,
RIGHT, SCOOB?

17:04.624 --> 17:06.693
REAH. BUMMER.

17:06.759 --> 17:09.296
[BOTH CRYING]

17:11.331 --> 17:13.500
OH, NO! SCOOBY-DOO!

17:13.566 --> 17:16.469
THE ANCIENT ONE'S
CURSE GOT YOU, TOO!

17:16.536 --> 17:17.804
Velma: NOT QUITE.

17:17.870 --> 17:19.472
HUH?
YOU'RE ALL GIANTS!

17:19.539 --> 17:23.110
OH, MAN, HOW ARE WE
ALL GONNA FIT INTO
THE MYSTERY MACHINE?

17:23.176 --> 17:25.512
DON'T WORRY, SHAG.
WE'RE NOT BIG.

17:25.578 --> 17:26.846
TOKYO'S JUST LITTLE.

17:26.913 --> 17:29.015
Velma: SEE?
WE'RE STANDING
IN THE MIDDLE

17:29.082 --> 17:30.817
OF A DETAILED MODEL
OF TOKYO.

17:30.883 --> 17:33.920
WE FOLLOWED DOGBOT
TO THIS ABANDONED
MOVIE STUDIO.

17:33.986 --> 17:36.656
THEY USED TO
MAKE MOVIES ABOUT
GIANT MONSTERS HERE.

17:36.723 --> 17:38.891
THIS PROVES YOU'RE NOT
THE MONSTER AT ALL.

17:38.958 --> 17:40.427
LIKE, IF NOT ME,

17:40.493 --> 17:44.597
WHO OR WHAT'S BEEN
RUNNING AROUND IN
SIZE 900 SNEAKERS?

17:44.664 --> 17:46.466
SOMETHING TELLS ME
WE'LL HAVE OUR ANSWER

17:46.533 --> 17:49.336
WHEN WE FIND OUT
WHO ORDERED DOGBOT
TO BRING YOU HERE.

17:49.402 --> 17:52.004
AND THE BEST PLACE
TO GET TO THE BOTTOM
OF THAT MYSTERY

17:52.071 --> 17:54.141
IS RIGHT BACK
WHERE WE STARTED--

17:54.207 --> 17:55.708
AT THE ROBOTICS FACTORY.

17:55.775 --> 17:58.778
NOW, ALL WE HAVE
TO DO IS SEARCH
THIS PLACE FOR--

17:58.845 --> 18:00.046
LOOK!
THERE'S ELLIOT

18:00.113 --> 18:01.948
KISSING UP
TO DR. ONODERA.

18:02.014 --> 18:03.416
WHY, THAT CHICKEN.

18:03.483 --> 18:06.186
MAYBE ELLIOT
KNOWS THE TRUTH
ABOUT THE MONSTER.

18:06.253 --> 18:07.554
WE BETTER ASK HIM.

18:07.620 --> 18:11.124
OR BETTER YET, ME!
UH--UH, HIM!

18:12.058 --> 18:14.561
[ROARS]
ZOINKS!

18:46.092 --> 18:49.396
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

18:49.462 --> 18:51.198
NOW LET'S SEE
WHO'S REALLY BEHIND

18:51.264 --> 18:53.800
THE ATTACK OF
THE 30-FOOT SHAGGY.

18:59.005 --> 19:01.308
All: PROFESSOR POMFRIT!

19:02.242 --> 19:03.410
I HATED TO ADMIT IT,

19:03.476 --> 19:05.412
BUT I KNEW IT MUST BE
THE PROFESSOR.

19:05.478 --> 19:07.780
THE MONSTER
DIDN'T SHOW UP
UNTIL WE DID.

19:07.847 --> 19:10.950
HE SAW THE CONFLICT
BETWEEN THE ANCIENT ONE
AND ONODERA

19:11.017 --> 19:14.187
AND USED
THE GIANT MONSTER LEGEND
TO FRAME SHAGGY.

19:14.254 --> 19:16.889
WHEN SHAGGY ATE
THE CURSED PIZZA,

19:16.956 --> 19:20.893
POMFRIT RIGGED DOGBOT
TO RESPOND TO HIS
REMOTE COMMANDS...

19:20.960 --> 19:24.264
AND GET THE SLEEPING
SHAGGY AWAY
FROM THE ACTION

19:24.331 --> 19:26.766
SO WE THOUGHT
HE WAS THE MONSTER.

19:26.833 --> 19:28.368
BUT, LIKE, WHY?

19:28.435 --> 19:30.537
BECAUSE EVERYTHING HE HAD
SHOULD BE MINE.

19:30.603 --> 19:33.806
WHY'S HE RICH WHEN
I'M JUST AN UNDERPAID
HIGH SCHOOL TEACHER?

19:33.873 --> 19:36.743
SOMEBODY'S FAVORITE
HIGH SCHOOL TEACHER.

19:36.809 --> 19:39.078
[SIGHS] YOU'RE
A BRILLIANT GIRL,
VELMA.

19:39.145 --> 19:40.980
YOU WERE
MY PRIZE STUDENT,

19:41.047 --> 19:43.082
AND I USED YOUR
INGENIOUS INVENTION

19:43.149 --> 19:44.984
FOR MY OWN
SELFISH ENDS.

19:45.051 --> 19:46.586
I'M VERY SORRY.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.421
HE WOULD'VE
GOTTEN AWAY
WITH IT, TOO,

19:48.488 --> 19:50.557
IF IT WEREN'T
FOR THOSE
MEDDLING KIDS.

19:50.623 --> 19:52.992
BUT, WHAT OF
THE ANCIENT ONE?

19:53.059 --> 19:55.428
SURELY HE HAD A HAND
IN ALL OF THIS.

19:55.495 --> 19:58.498
THERE'S
NO SUCH THING
AS THE ANCIENT ONE.

19:58.565 --> 20:01.067
YOU MEAN HE WAS...
[GULP] A SPIRIT?

20:01.133 --> 20:02.535
WHATEVER HE WAS,

20:02.602 --> 20:04.103
I'M SURE HE'LL BE
PLEASED TO KNOW

20:04.170 --> 20:06.939
THAT I'VE DECIDED
TO BUILD A NEW WHARF
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

20:07.006 --> 20:10.243
AFTER ALL THIS,
I DON'T WANT TO SEE
ANYTHING DESTROYED.

20:10.310 --> 20:12.178
HERE, ELLIOT,

20:12.245 --> 20:14.381
A DOG YOU WON'T BE
ALLERGIC TO.

20:14.447 --> 20:16.649
WHAT? YOU'RE
GIVING HIM TO ME?

20:16.716 --> 20:18.818
MY OWN DOG! WOW!

20:18.885 --> 20:22.455
I--HEH.
THANKS, VELMA.

20:22.522 --> 20:24.591
THAT WAS REALLY SWEET
OF YOU, VELMA.

20:24.657 --> 20:26.826
BUT AREN'T YOU
GOING TO MISS DOGBOT?

20:26.893 --> 20:30.963
NO. I MAY HAVE
GIVEN DOGBOT
A SUPERSIZED BRAIN,

20:31.030 --> 20:32.465
BUT THAT JUST
CAN'T COMPETE

20:32.532 --> 20:34.667
WITH SCOOBY-DOO'S
SUPERSIZED HEART.

20:34.734 --> 20:37.169
All: AWW!

20:37.236 --> 20:39.572
SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOO!
